Q39. (Theory) What is an IoT gateway? Draw a simple diagram showing the relationship 
between: IoT Sensor Nodes → Gateway → Cloud → User Application. What protocols are 
typically used at each layer? (2 marks) 

An IoT Gateway is a device that acts as a bridge between IoT sensor nodes and the cloud. 
It collects data from sensors, processes or filters it if required, and then sends it to the cloud for storage and analysis. 
The gateway also receives commands from the cloud and forwards them to the IoT devices.

Working

The sensor nodes collect data such as temperature, humidity, or soil moisture and send it to the gateway. 
The gateway forwards the data to the cloud using internet protocols. 
The cloud stores and analyzes the data, and users can view the information through a mobile app or web application.
An IoT Gateway is an intermediary device that connects IoT sensors to the cloud. It collects data from sensors, processes it, and sends it to the cloud.
Common protocols include Zigbee, LoRa, BLE, MQTT, and HTTP/HTTPS.

